-- Vale, Usiminas, CSN Win Rulings Against Mining Taxes, Globo Says
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-06-06T12:11:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/vale-usiminas-csn-win-rulings-against-mining-taxes-globo-says.html
Vale SA (VALE3) ,  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas
Gerais SA  and  Cia. Siderurgica Nacional SA (CSNA3)  won court injunctions
to avert a combined 1.5 billion reais ($741.7 million) of annual
mining taxes in two Brazilian states, O Globo reported.  Usiminas and CSN were granted injunctions in the
southeastern state of  Minas Gerais , while Vale won a ruling in
the northern Para state, the Rio de Janeiro-based newspaper
said.  State governments may appeal the decisions, O Globo said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
